description.value: This is a grouping value set that includes terms related to hypertensive disorders of pregnancy which include pre-existing hypertension, chronic hypertension, hypertensive chronic kidney disease, essential hypertension, hypertension diagnosed during the course of pregnancy and diagnoses of pre-eclampsia and eclampsia.

purpose.value: This grouping value set groups Hypertensive Disorders of Pregnancy codes from the SNOMED-CT and ICD-10 codesystems.
